{"author":{"id":"cff9ab1d2ee9741039b2a60d90cca378a5320ba753398f6f3df8d03abcebee1b"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1770886152,"nonce":"IHdPLNDMtb/KPjHfNbvdob6W/eM=","metadata":{"github-id":"I_kwDORKr0287qSByi","github-url":"https://github.com/bonanzahq/bonanza/issues/44","origin":"github"},"title":"Configure ActionMailer for Mailpit (dev) and SMTP relay (prod)","message":"Borrower creation fails silently because ActionMailer isn't configured in the Docker environment.\n\n**Root cause:** When creating a borrower, send_confirmation_pending_email calls create_token then BorrowerMailer.confirm_email.deliver_now. The mailer fails, the rescue catches the exception, and raise ActiveRecord::Rollback rolls back the token save. The borrower exists but email_token is nil, which causes a UrlGenerationError on the borrower show page (send_confirm_email_path requires a non-nil token).\n\n**What needs to happen:**\n- Development: configure ActionMailer to deliver via Mailpit (already in docker-compose on port 8025, just needs Rails config)\n- Production: configure ActionMailer to use the FHP SMTP relay\n\n**Affected files:**\n- config/environments/development.rb (add Mailpit SMTP config)\n- config/environments/production.rb (add FHP SMTP relay config)\n- app/models/borrower.rb:36-43 (send_confirmation_pending_email)\n- app/views/borrowers/_borrower.html.erb:31 (crashes when email_token is nil)\n\n**Secondary issue:** The view should guard against nil email_token rather than crashing, regardless of mail config.","files":null}]}